  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Hygiene, Sanitation and Water Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">About 20 percent of Bangladesh&#x92;s population has no access to safe drinking water; some 40 percent are deprived of improved sanitation facilities. The Hygiene, Sanitation and Water Fund, set up in 2007 by the leading international development agencies, partners with competent local government institutions to provide efficient and state-of-the-art WatSan solutions for millions of Bangladeshi households. The present proposal undertakes to co-finance the successful Fund for the period of 2012 through 2015.</narrative>
  </description>
